tafsir[7]{c,v,t}:
  26,115,"“I am only a clear warner; I warn you of the punishment of Allah.”"
  26,123,"The people of ‘Ād disbelived in all the messengers by their rejection of Hud (peace be upon him)."
  26,126,"“So be mindful of Allah by fulfilling His commandments and refrain from that which He has prohibited. And obey me in whatever I have commanded you with and forbidden you from.”"
  26,131,"“So be mindful of Allah by fulfilling His commandments and refrain from that which He has prohibited. And obey me in whatever I command you with and forbid you from.”"
  26,132,"“And fear the wrath of Allah who has granted you everything which you know well.”"
  26,134,"“And He granted you gardens and flowing streams.”"
  26,135,"O my people! I fear the punishment of the great day over you: the Day of Judgement."